This project will provide nine (9) new informational kiosks throughout the De Anza campus, including associated electrical and site work. The kiosks will provide directional location and building maps, student activity information, and community information for students, staff, and the general public. Noll and Tam Architects prepared the bid documents for the work.
 
The bid was legally advertised to contractors on January 23 and January 30, 2015. The “Invitation to Bid” was also sent to nine (9) builder’s exchanges and advertised in the San Jose Post-Record well as posted on “BidNet” at www.govbids.com.  Bids were publicly opened and read on March 5, 2015 in the Purchasing Services office. Six (6) contractors submitted bids. Bid results are below:
	 
BID RESULTS
 
